:%s/\ class=".*"//g will remove all class attributes from the file.<br>
:%s - is run the search and replace command using the entire buffer (%) as the range<br><br>
\ class=" - this looks for the string class=" (specifically with a space infront of the word class)<br><br>
. - matches any character<br>
* - matches any amount of times, thus .* matches any character any amount of times<br><br>
" - ends the search pattern as it closes the class attribute<br>
// - replace the pattern with nothing (delete it)<br>
g - do it for every pattern match, not just first match per line
